					<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.behaviormodel.org/">BJ Fogg's Behavior Model</a> by Dr. BJ Fogg, founder of the Persuasive Technology Lab at Stanford University</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flow_(psychology)">Flow</a> - concept introduced by Dr. Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi, former head of the department of psychology at the University of Chicago. More information in the book <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/Flow-The-Psychology-Optimal-Experience/dp/0061339202">"Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience"</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deliberate_practice#Deliberate_practice">Deliberate Practice</a> - concept introduced by Dr. K. Anders Ericsson, Professor of Psychology at Florida State University. More information in the book <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.amazon.com/Talent-Overrated-World-Class-Performers-EverybodyElse/dp/1591842948">"Talent Is Overrated: What Really Separates World-Class Performers from Everybody Else"</a></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rrkrvAUbU9Y">The Surprising Science of Motivation</a> - TED Talk by Daniel Pink (Author of <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.danpink.com/drive">Drive</a>)</p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/david_perry_on_videogames.html">Are Games Better Than Life?</a>- TED Talk by David Perry</p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ted.com/talks/tom_chatfield_7_ways_games_reward_the_brain.html">Ways that games reward the brain</a>- TED Talk by Tom Chatfield, Chatfield looks into the ways that games engage the brain through intrinsic reward systems within the brain.</p></li>
</ul>

